[2] France: 27th vCJD case (2nd in 2012)
Date: Tue 10 Jul 2012
Source: Enviro2b [in French, trans. Mod.CP, edited]
http://www.enviro2b.com/2012/07/10/maladie-de-creutzfeldt-jacob-un-nouveau-cas-humain-signale/


A new case (the 27th) of Variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease in France
--------------------------------------------------------------------
A new case of variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease [vCJD], the human form of bovine spongiform encephalopathy [BSE] has been diagnosed in France. The case is a 27-year-old under person who has been under observation since 1996. vCJD is associated with the consumption of bovine neural and other tissues. VCJD has now been diagnosed in 27 people in France. This case is the 2nd recorded in France during 2012. Both vCJD cases identified in France in 2012 remain alive, whereas the 25 cases diagnosed previously have all died.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In June 2012 a new case of variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (vCJD), was identified in France, being the 26th case since 1996, and the 1st new case for 3 years. Of these 26 probable or confirmed cases of vCJD in France (12 men and 14 women), all except the most recent case have died.

The 25 fatal cases prior to this year occurred in 1996 (1 case), 2000 (1 case), 2001 (1 case), 2002 (3 cases), 2004 (2 cases) 2005 (6 cases) in 2006 (6 cases), in 2007 (3 cases), and 2009 (2 cases). The median age at death or diagnosis was 37 years (ranging from 19 to 58 years). Of these 26 victims, 8 patients lived in the Ile-de-France and 18 in the provinces. One victim had regularly resided in the UK during a 10-year period since 1987.

For those interested, the Table of the Total Number and Distribution of Human vCJD Cases, worldwide, has been updated now to include these 2 new French cases and is available at http://www.cjd.ed.ac.uk/vcjdworld.htm.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of France can be found at http://healthmap.org/r/1oxc. -Mod.CP]

